    {
      "id": 26,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [-900, -920],
      "size": [560, 200],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 24,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Ca ne bouge pas / juste un zoom ?\n\n1. **Verifie le UNET** : il DOIT s'appeler `flux1-dev-kontext_...` — PAS `flux1-dev` ni Z-Image.\n2. **Regarde `kontext_edit/`** dans output — pas le preview \"recadrage\".\n3. **Test radical** : prompt = `Change the jacket to bright yellow` — si rien ne change, mauvais modele.\n4. **Guidance** etait a 2.5 (trop bas) → maintenant **4.0**. Monte a 5 si edit faible.\n5. **FluxKontextImageScale** recadre toujours un peu — c'est normal, ce n'est pas l'edit.\n6. **Mute le noeud ZiT polish** pour tester Kontext seul.\n7. **Nunchaku** : baisse cache_threshold ou desactive si image quasi identique."
      ],
      "color": "#533",
      "bgcolor": "#322",
      "title": "DEPANNAGE — prompt ignore"
    },
    {
      "id": 23,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [-900, -680],
      "size": [520, 220],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 22,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Modeles a telecharger (ComfyUI-Shared/models)\n\n**diffusion_models/** flux1-dev-kontext_fp8_scaled.safetensors\nhttps://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/flux1-kontext-dev_ComfyUI\n\n**text_encoders/** clip_l.safetensors + t5xxl_fp8_e4m3fn_scaled.safetensors\n\n**vae/** ae.safetensors (deja present pour Z-Image)\n\n### 16 Go VRAM (RTX 5080)\nfp8_scaled demande ~20 Go. Si OOM sur l'etape Kontext :\n1. Installe **ComfyUI-nunchaku**\n2. Remplace UNETLoader par **NunchakuFluxDiTLoader** avec **svdq-fp4** (Blackwell 50-series)\n3. Ou active cpu_offload dans Nunchaku\n\nDoc : docs.comfy.org/tutorials/flux/flux-1-kontext-dev"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653",
      "title": "Telechargements + VRAM"
    },
    {
      "id": 24,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [240, 360],
      "size": [720, 420],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 23,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Flux Kontext — garder le visage, changer le reste\n\n**Structure du prompt (EN anglais)** :\n1. **Change [ce que tu veux]** en premier\n2. **While maintaining the exact same facial features, hairstyle, and expression**\n3. Decris la personne (cheveux, yeux, geste…) — pas \"she\", sois precis\n4. **Keep [background/pose] unchanged** si tu veux les garder\n\n**Exemples**\n- Corps : `Change her body to be noticeably slimmer while maintaining the exact same facial features...`\n- Vetement : `Change the denim jacket to a red leather jacket while preserving facial features...`\n- Fond : `Change the background to a sunny beach while keeping the person in the exact same position, scale, and pose`\n\n**Evite** : `Transform into a Viking` → le visage part. Prefere : `Change clothes to viking armor while preserving facial features`.\n\n**Etape 1** Kontext fait l'edit instructionnel.\n**Etape 2** ZiT polish x2 remet la qualite Z-Image sans re-deformer (enhance quality, denoise 0).\n\n**Astuce** : edits complexes = 2 passes Kontext (fond puis vetement), puis polish ZiT une fois."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653",
      "title": "Technique prompt identite"
    }
  ],
